Create Year Column 14  4) Create Year column

              Year text column

      - (1) Click to Dim_JRP_Jobs table ---> Click to Created column

      - (2) On ribbon click Add column ---> Click Date ---> choose Year

      - (3) On ribbon click Transform ---> Change the data type to Text ( we change this one to data type of text

                because if we use datatype of Date it only show the data of year "1905)

      - (4) Right click to Year column ---> choose Rename ---> change the column name to Year text 


          

            Create Year column

      - (1) Click to Year column

      - (2) On ribbon click Add Column ---> Click Custom Column

      - (3) In New column name box ---> type Year

      - (4) In Custom column formula  box ---> type = "1/1/" & ---> Click to Year text column (on the right) ---> click insert ---     >                  -- OK

            

   1) Create Measure table to store all the Measures

    This Step help us easier to find the Measures that we created.

     - (1) Click to Home ---> Click to Enter Data

-   - (2) Change the table name to MEASURE TABLE

     - (3) Click to Load
